com.cyc.base.inference

Interface InferenceResultSet

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, ResultSet, Wrapper
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractResultSet, DefaultResultSet

    public interface InferenceResultSet
extends ResultSet
    InferenceResultSet defines an interface for easy access and manipulation of inference results. It tries to closely mimic the java.sql.ResultSet class.

    • Method Detail

      • close

        void close()
           throws CycTimeOutException,
                  CycApiException
        Releases this InferenceResultSet object's server side inference resources. Failure to close a result set may leave significant resources hanging around the server until the client CycAccess object is closed.

        Calling the method close on a InferenceResultSet object that is already closed is a no-op.

        Specified by:
        close in interface AutoCloseable
        Specified by:
        close in interface ResultSet
        Throws:
        CycTimeOutException - if doesn't get a response from the server before an excessive amount of time has elapsed
        CycApiException - if an internal server error occurs

      • getCloseTimeout

        long getCloseTimeout()
        Returns the timeout for the close() method. By default, returns the timeout of the InferenceWorker which returned this object, or this class's own internal default (typically 10,000 milliseconds), whichever is greater. This value may be changed by calling setCloseTimeout(Long).
        Returns:
        timeout in milliseconds

      • setCloseTimeout

        void setCloseTimeout(Long timeoutMS)
        Set the timeout for the close() method returned by getCloseTimeout(). Specifying a non-null value here will, naturally, override the default value. Specifying a null value will clear the overridden value, and getCloseTimeout() will return its usual default.
        Parameters:
        timeoutMS - timeout in milliseconds

      • getBoolean

        boolean getBoolean(CycVariable col)
                   throws CycApiException,
                          IllegalArgumentException,
                          ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException,
                          ClassCastException
        Returns, as a boolean, the value at the current row and at the column identified by col which should be a CycVariable in the original query. Returns null if no value is set for the current row and given column.

        Note: Use the method int colIindex = findColumn(col) once and the version of this method that takes an integer for maximum performance.

        Parameters:
        col - the name of the variable that represents the column of interest
        Returns:
        the value, as a boolean, at the current row and at the column identified by the col which is a CycVariable in the original query. Returns null, if no value is set for the current row and given column.
        Throws:
        CycApiException - if called on a closed result set
        IllegalArgumentException - if col is not valid
        ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException - if the current cursor is not on a valid row
        ClassCastException - if the value is not convertible to a boolean

        Returns, as a CycObject, the value at the current row and at the column identified by colIndex. Returns null if no value is set for the current row and given column. Note: literal strings and numbers are not CycObjects and can possibly be returned by some inferences.
